WEBVTT

00:10.600 --> 00:11.829
<i>Previously on</i> Dexter:

00:12.040 --> 00:13.793
Who's the guy that dropped you off?

00:14.000 --> 00:15.514
We didn't sleep together.

00:15.720 --> 00:17.757
You are certainly allowed
to be a player.

00:19.280 --> 00:21.192
You remember Cassie, right?
Yeah.

00:21.400 --> 00:22.436
New neighbour. Hi.
Hi.

00:22.640 --> 00:24.120
I kind of need to leave.

00:24.320 --> 00:26.755
I'll take care of Jamie.
Maybe we could reschedule?

00:27.000 --> 00:28.559
Yeah. I'd like that.

00:29.040 --> 00:30.872
Any reason why you
haven't taken the exam?

00:31.080 --> 00:33.959
I got your brother on my ass
about taking the sergeant's test--

00:34.160 --> 00:36.231
What is so wrong about
bettering yourself?

00:36.440 --> 00:37.635
You nailed it, bro.

00:37.840 --> 00:41.231
Is he your choice for sergeant?
I'm ready for more responsibility.

00:41.440 --> 00:43.830
I want you to strongly consider
making her sergeant.

00:44.040 --> 00:45.360
I think you may be my father.

00:45.600 --> 00:49.150
Family showing up out of nowhere?
A lot of times, they want something.

00:49.400 --> 00:51.551
I you to do a background check
on someone.

00:51.760 --> 00:54.320
You think she's here to rip you off?
I don't know.

00:54.720 --> 00:55.836
Norma Rivera.

00:56.040 --> 00:58.794
She'd been having an affair
with the boss, Ed Hamilton.

00:59.000 --> 01:00.957
Dad, what's going on?
The Hamilton's son.

01:01.200 --> 01:03.351
Did you go to where
Norma Rivera was killed?

01:03.560 --> 01:06.758
I did.
What did you see in your analysis?

01:07.000 --> 01:08.798
Leave the kid alone.
He killed her.

01:09.040 --> 01:11.191
You don't know that.
Your only witness recanted.

01:11.400 --> 01:13.756
No reason to make enemies
unless we really have to.

01:13.960 --> 01:15.792
Where's Yates?

01:16.000 --> 01:18.799
So this is finally over.
My tormenter's dead.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.276
Thanks to you, Dexter.
And Deb.

01:21.480 --> 01:23.711
I'm glad you found your way
back to each other.

01:23.920 --> 01:25.798
Well, the family that kills together...

01:26.000 --> 01:28.959
A few days ago, everything seemed
hopeless between Deb and me.

01:29.160 --> 01:31.436
But through Dr. Vogel,
I've got my sister back.

01:31.640 --> 01:33.120
It's beautiful out here, Dexter.

01:33.360 --> 01:34.919
I wanted to be with family.

03:37.520 --> 03:38.795
<i>Accidents happen,</i>

03:39.000 --> 03:41.151
<i>shattering our sense of control,</i>

03:41.400 --> 03:43.278
<i>if not our lives.</i>

03:46.600 --> 03:49.035
<i>It's no accident
that Zach Hamilton is here.</i>

03:49.240 --> 03:52.119
<i>He's drawn to blood, like me.</i>

03:53.640 --> 03:56.519
<i>Did he kill Norma Rivera?</i>

04:07.760 --> 04:11.356
<i>After a week of vetting him, I haven't
been able to find definitive proof.</i>

04:17.519 --> 04:21.673
<i>But I'm sure if I keep following him
the truth will become clear.</i>

04:38.920 --> 04:40.559
<i>Or it could get murkier.</i>

05:14.960 --> 05:16.076
Dexter.

05:16.280 --> 05:18.431
Have you taken on
Zach Hamilton as a patient?

05:18.640 --> 05:19.835
It's nice to see you too.

05:20.040 --> 05:23.158
I have to protect you from another
murderer? How did he get to you?

05:23.640 --> 05:24.960
His father contacted me

05:25.160 --> 05:28.915
because of my reputation
for working with psychopaths.

05:29.160 --> 05:33.234
He's concerned about his son's
behaviour, his propensity for violence.

05:33.440 --> 05:34.874
It's more than a propensity.

05:35.080 --> 05:38.312
I think Zach Hamilton
killed Norma Rivera.

05:39.440 --> 05:42.478
And I take it that
you followed him here today

05:42.680 --> 05:44.672
because you're planning
to kill him?

05:44.880 --> 05:48.078
The thought had crossed my mind,
yes, if I can find solid proof.

05:48.560 --> 05:51.871
Well, then it would seem
that we have a conflict of interest.

05:54.240 --> 05:56.197
I don't believe this.

05:57.200 --> 06:00.716
You're going to work with another killer
after what happened with Yates?

06:01.080 --> 06:03.834
Dexter, I appreciate your concern,

06:04.040 --> 06:07.829
but I'm not going to talk about
Zach Hamilton with you any further.

06:08.720 --> 06:10.120
It wouldn't be ethical.

06:10.320 --> 06:12.437
Suddenly,
you're worried about ethics?

06:12.680 --> 06:15.070
I know. I threw them out
the window when I met you

06:15.280 --> 06:17.351
because my life was on the line.

06:17.640 --> 06:19.518
Now the threat is over.

06:19.720 --> 06:21.916
You're bringing another threat
into your life.

06:22.120 --> 06:25.397
It's my work. What can I say?

06:25.880 --> 06:27.951
I treat dangerous people.

06:28.200 --> 06:29.793
It's a hazard of the job.

06:30.000 --> 06:31.514
Besides, you have no proof

06:31.720 --> 06:33.951
that Zach Hamilton
is guilty of anything.

06:34.680 --> 06:35.796
I will.

06:36.280 --> 06:37.634
If you do,

06:37.840 --> 06:39.797
then come to see me first,

06:40.040 --> 06:41.554
before you do anything,

06:41.760 --> 06:44.195
and we'll have
another conversation.

06:45.320 --> 06:47.232
Would you do me that favour?

06:48.400 --> 06:49.959
We'll see.

07:02.440 --> 07:04.909
Maybe this is why
she tracked me down, for money.

07:05.120 --> 07:06.873
You don't know that.

07:07.080 --> 07:09.640
I mean, maybe she genuinely
wanted to get to know you.

07:09.840 --> 07:12.560
What, at the same time
her Hyundai's being repossessed?

07:12.760 --> 07:15.070
Has she asked you for money?
No.

07:15.280 --> 07:18.557
But she always seems to be missing
her purse when the check comes.

07:23.040 --> 07:26.590
I thought we had a real connection.
You like having Niki in your life?

07:27.800 --> 07:29.632
I do.
Then why don't you wait it out

07:29.880 --> 07:31.997
and see how it plays out?

07:32.280 --> 07:35.114
In the meantime,
you can enjoy her company.

07:38.280 --> 07:39.634
Okay.

07:46.040 --> 07:47.599
Hm, heh.
Thanks, Deb.

07:47.760 --> 07:49.399
Welcome.

07:51.640 --> 07:54.360
Deb, got a new case.

07:55.560 --> 07:59.520
Let me guess, someone suspects their
significant other is fucking around.

08:00.120 --> 08:03.511
Yeah, but this one
is a bit different.

08:03.720 --> 08:06.519
How?
Because the person is me

08:06.720 --> 08:08.200
and the significant other

08:08.400 --> 08:11.040
is my sister's ass-chasing,
shithead boyfriend.

08:11.240 --> 08:13.072
Kevin Wyman, notorious player,

08:13.280 --> 08:16.193
frequents a singles bar in a hotel
where he keeps a suite.

08:17.000 --> 08:18.878
Have you tried talking to her?

08:19.080 --> 08:20.150
Susan doesn't listen to me.

08:20.360 --> 08:22.591
It'd just push her
more quickly into his arms.

08:22.800 --> 08:24.029
So that's off the table.

08:24.240 --> 08:27.756
Well, going behind her back
seems kind of fucked up.

08:27.960 --> 08:30.680
It's gotta be this way.
I gotta catch this guy in the act.

08:30.880 --> 08:32.599
Okay, but you're doing it
by yourself.

08:32.799 --> 08:34.200
I need your help on this, Deb.

08:34.360 --> 08:35.510
It'd be a lot less conspicuous

08:35.679 --> 08:37.399
if we work this as a couple.

08:37.600 --> 08:39.751
Well, I'm not sure if I'm comfortable.

08:39.960 --> 08:42.155
Well, are you comfortable
getting a pay cheque?

08:45.520 --> 08:46.795
Okay, boss.

08:48.760 --> 08:50.433
Thank you.

08:53.600 --> 08:55.671
Where does this piece go?

08:57.040 --> 08:58.759
Right here.

08:59.480 --> 09:00.800
Very good.

09:01.000 --> 09:02.593
Dex?

09:02.840 --> 09:05.355
Don't forget, my birthday picnic's
in a few days, okay?

09:05.600 --> 09:08.069
On the beach, outside of Papa's.
Bring Harrison.

09:08.280 --> 09:10.158
Yeah, we'll be there.
Great.

09:10.400 --> 09:13.313
You know who else
will be there? Cassie.

09:13.520 --> 09:14.749
I heard you have a date with her.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.076
No, it's not a date.

09:16.320 --> 09:20.155
I felt like I owed her one after we both
bailed on your dinner the other night.

09:20.360 --> 09:22.511
Why won't you just admit
that you like her

09:22.720 --> 09:24.712
and that I am an
awesome matchmaker?

09:24.960 --> 09:28.271
I admit that you're an awesome nanny.
You'll have to settle for that.

09:28.480 --> 09:31.552
We'll revisit this after the date.

09:31.880 --> 09:33.360
Oh, by the way,

09:33.560 --> 09:35.233
the TV remote has

09:35.440 --> 09:36.510
been missing since yesterday.

09:36.760 --> 09:38.433
I think somebody hid it

09:38.680 --> 09:41.514
but I can't get anything
out of him.

09:42.160 --> 09:44.117
Harrison, did you
take the TV remote?

09:44.320 --> 09:45.595
No.

09:45.800 --> 09:48.554
Do you know where it is?
No.

09:49.040 --> 09:50.156
He says he didn't take it.

09:50.400 --> 09:51.470
Right.

09:51.680 --> 09:54.195
Guess I'll just keep looking for it.

09:57.680 --> 10:00.115
Homicide in Liberty City.

10:00.320 --> 10:03.358
It looks like you're gonna have
to finish that puzzle on your own.

10:03.560 --> 10:05.597
I'm doing all the work anyway.

10:06.600 --> 10:08.956
Yeah, you are.

10:09.160 --> 10:11.072
Bye.
Bye.

10:20.040 --> 10:21.759
Welcome to spatter-land.

10:21.960 --> 10:23.314
Hope you brought extra string.

10:23.560 --> 10:25.597
Never leave home without it.

10:27.200 --> 10:28.350
Good news.

10:28.600 --> 10:30.637
We have the victim's boyfriend
in custody.

10:30.840 --> 10:33.309
A witness saw him
taking off from the scene,

10:33.520 --> 10:35.512
and he forgot to change
his bloody socks.

10:35.720 --> 10:37.473
Heh. God bless stupid killers.

10:51.680 --> 10:53.353
<i>Once again, drawn to blood.</i>

10:54.280 --> 10:57.557
<i>Looks like Zach has just given me
the in I need.</i>

11:17.720 --> 11:20.076
Zach Hamilton, right?

11:20.360 --> 11:21.953
You were at my house.

11:22.200 --> 11:23.316
That's right.

11:23.880 --> 11:26.315
You guys find out
who killed Norma?

11:26.840 --> 11:29.674
No luck. It's a dead end.

11:32.320 --> 11:33.800
You like to shoot crime scenes?

11:34.040 --> 11:36.919
Yeah, I got a police scanner
app on my phone.

11:37.120 --> 11:38.600
Better than playing video games.

11:38.840 --> 11:41.594
You ever been on the other side
of the yellow tape?

11:42.120 --> 11:44.760
Nope.
This is as close as I've gotten.

11:45.640 --> 11:47.950
Well, come on.

11:49.800 --> 11:53.111
Are you serious?
Yeah, just don't touch anything.

12:00.960 --> 12:02.553
Whoa.

12:04.520 --> 12:06.432
This is amazing.

12:06.840 --> 12:10.038
<i>I remember that feeling.
Awe, wonder.</i>

12:10.240 --> 12:11.356
<i>It only fed the urge.</i>

12:11.560 --> 12:14.029
Hey, can I take some pictures?

12:15.880 --> 12:19.556
It's usually against protocol,

12:19.800 --> 12:21.029
but what the hell? Go ahead.

12:21.360 --> 12:23.397
Cool. Thanks.

12:25.440 --> 12:28.990
So, what happened to her?

12:29.200 --> 12:30.714
She was stabbed.

12:30.920 --> 12:33.435
Yeah, obviously.
But, like, you know, how?

12:33.920 --> 12:36.719
<i>If I open up to him,
maybe he'll open up to me.</i>

12:36.920 --> 12:38.434
Come on. I can handle it.

12:42.040 --> 12:44.077
Well, the victim
tried to defend herself.

12:44.320 --> 12:46.232
There were defensive
wounds on her body

12:46.440 --> 12:50.559
but you can also tell by these
big, round drops on the ground.

12:54.120 --> 12:55.998
And this multiple cast-off spatter

12:56.200 --> 12:59.352
suggests that she was
stabbed several times.

12:59.560 --> 13:02.280
And the arterial spurting here

13:02.480 --> 13:05.359
indicates that the killer
severed her carotid artery

13:05.560 --> 13:07.233
with the first stab.

13:09.160 --> 13:11.959
You can tell all that
just by looking at the blood?

13:12.840 --> 13:13.990
Pretty much.

13:14.800 --> 13:16.473
Awesome.

13:18.680 --> 13:20.831
So I heard you caught
the guy who did it.

13:21.040 --> 13:22.872
Yeah, her boyfriend.
How?

13:23.080 --> 13:26.073
He was sloppy.
Left a bloody print and DNA.

13:26.320 --> 13:28.471
He was spotted
driving away from the scene.

13:28.680 --> 13:30.353
Oh, yeah? What kind of car?

13:30.560 --> 13:32.916
<i>Must have heard his Porsche
was seen at Norma's apartment.</i>

13:33.160 --> 13:34.355
No one noticed.

13:39.280 --> 13:41.272
So the killer,

13:42.280 --> 13:44.431
he should've worn gloves
and long sleeves,

13:44.640 --> 13:46.120
made sure
he was covered up.

13:46.320 --> 13:49.119
<i>He's making this a teaching moment.</i>

13:49.840 --> 13:52.275
Well, yeah, if he was smart.

13:53.680 --> 13:54.875
<i>The kid's a quick study,</i>

13:55.080 --> 13:57.515
<i>but that doesn't prove
he killed Norma Rivera.</i>

13:59.080 --> 14:03.711
So, hey, I gotta get going,
but thanks.

14:04.400 --> 14:07.632
Hey, why don't you give me a call
when you print those up?

14:07.840 --> 14:09.832
I'd love to take a look.

14:10.560 --> 14:13.519
Yeah.
Yeah, I guess I could do that.

14:18.320 --> 14:20.755
<i>Time to make another connection.</i>

14:26.560 --> 14:29.712
Here you go.
Thank you.

14:29.920 --> 14:32.230
Thank you
for doing this with me.

14:32.440 --> 14:35.558
When you own a food truck, you
have to scope out the competition.

14:35.760 --> 14:37.274
Plus I just really love to eat.

14:37.520 --> 14:38.556
Yeah, no problem.

14:38.760 --> 14:41.036
I wouldn't miss these peanut butter
and Nutella fries for anything.

14:41.240 --> 14:42.754
Mm-hm.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.516
So you're indulging me
in my favourite pastime.

14:50.720 --> 14:52.359
What do you like to do for fun?

14:52.560 --> 14:54.995
You know, normal stuff.

14:55.640 --> 14:57.233
Like what?

14:58.320 --> 15:00.630
Um...
Heh, heh.

15:01.960 --> 15:03.917
I like spending time with my son.

15:04.120 --> 15:06.316
I already know you're
a great dad. What else?

15:08.200 --> 15:09.270
I love my job.

15:09.920 --> 15:12.560
But that's work.
What are you passionate about?

15:15.480 --> 15:16.994
I like to bowl.

15:17.200 --> 15:18.873
You're passionate about bowling?

15:20.880 --> 15:22.678
No. Heh.
Heh, heh.

15:22.880 --> 15:24.678
Of course not.

15:24.880 --> 15:27.475
I just do it for fun, once in a while.

15:29.280 --> 15:32.717
What about your weekends
or your free time?

15:34.160 --> 15:35.640
Oh, I have a boat.

15:35.840 --> 15:37.115
Oh, I love to sail.

15:37.720 --> 15:39.677
No, it's a motorboat.

15:39.880 --> 15:41.997
Oh. You water-ski?

15:42.320 --> 15:43.720
No.

15:43.960 --> 15:46.520
Race?
No.

15:47.360 --> 15:49.033
Do you scuba dive?

15:49.560 --> 15:50.994
No.

15:51.160 --> 15:53.755
Heh, heh.
What do you do on your boat?

15:55.160 --> 15:56.480
I just...

15:56.720 --> 15:59.679
Take it out and...

16:00.560 --> 16:02.552
Turn around and come back.

16:04.040 --> 16:05.076
That's it?

16:05.280 --> 16:07.556
<i>That's all I can tell you.</i>

16:08.120 --> 16:09.793
I think we may need
some alcohol.

16:10.880 --> 16:12.234
Right.

16:13.440 --> 16:16.035
<i>Dating is harder than I remember.</i>

16:23.040 --> 16:24.713
Oh, this guy is fucking pathetic.

16:24.960 --> 16:27.520
I get that you hate the guy,
but looking isn't cheating.

16:27.720 --> 16:29.632
It's a slow night.
Give him a minute.

16:32.520 --> 16:34.239
So you said Susan
doesn't listen.

16:34.440 --> 16:36.909
Does that mean you all
have a strained relationship?

16:37.120 --> 16:38.600
Not from my end, no.

16:39.560 --> 16:41.313
But from hers?

16:42.320 --> 16:43.959
Yeah, you know, probably.

16:44.720 --> 16:47.599
I mean, look, I couldn't wait
to get away from my old man,

16:47.800 --> 16:49.393
and Susan was just a kid.

16:49.600 --> 16:53.560
You know, I should have
at least picked up the phone.

16:54.640 --> 16:57.109
But I never did,
you know, so...

16:59.400 --> 17:01.790
Well, you can't undo the past.

17:03.360 --> 17:06.000
And families fuck you up.
That's just the way it is.

17:07.480 --> 17:10.119
I can stop Susan from fucking up her future.
I can do that.

17:14.079 --> 17:16.515
It looks like he's
packing it in for the night.

17:16.760 --> 17:19.116
If you wanna catch this guy,
why don't I set him up?

17:19.319 --> 17:22.392
We can see if he takes the bait.
No, I don't want you doing that.

17:22.640 --> 17:25.439
I worked Vice. I've done
worse than that before.

17:27.680 --> 17:29.751
I just need pictures
of him hitting on you.

17:29.960 --> 17:31.553
Certainly nothing
more than that.

17:31.760 --> 17:33.114
Are you sure?

17:33.360 --> 17:36.990
I mean, I could marry him,
maybe pop out a couple of babies.

17:38.400 --> 17:39.914
Let's go.

17:56.200 --> 17:58.192
Dexter, thanks for coming.
Sure.

17:58.960 --> 18:00.792
Couldn't wait to show you
these photos.

18:01.000 --> 18:02.912
Yeah, no problem.
It's on my way to work.

18:03.120 --> 18:04.236
Doughnut?

18:05.000 --> 18:06.229
Fucking A.

18:08.200 --> 18:09.236
Mm.

18:11.240 --> 18:12.959
Well?

18:16.040 --> 18:19.351
<i>He treats the blood
like a swimsuit model.</i>

18:20.160 --> 18:21.753
Well,

18:22.480 --> 18:24.119
very colourful.

18:24.320 --> 18:27.870
You know, a lot of photographers
like to mute down their reds.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.794
You know,
find it too distracting,

18:31.040 --> 18:33.350
but I like to ride the saturation.

18:33.520 --> 18:34.795
Hm.

18:36.560 --> 18:38.074
You think I overdid it?

18:38.760 --> 18:40.752
No way. These are you.

18:40.960 --> 18:42.474
That's the important thing.

18:42.720 --> 18:45.360
Well, I can work you up
some prints, if you want.

18:45.600 --> 18:46.954
I wouldn't have them
if it weren't for you.

18:47.160 --> 18:50.312
Actually, I think I have
plenty of my own.

18:52.520 --> 18:53.840
Right.

18:54.040 --> 18:56.475
Of course.
I forget it was a crime scene.

18:56.680 --> 19:00.594
Keep thinking that dead chick
spilled all that blood just for me.

19:07.520 --> 19:08.840
Who's she?

19:10.920 --> 19:12.434
Uh, it's nothing.

19:13.560 --> 19:16.359
Just a lens test.

19:16.560 --> 19:19.075
New 300 millimetre.
Fucking monster.

19:19.280 --> 19:20.270
Wow.

19:22.800 --> 19:24.120
Excuse me.

19:24.280 --> 19:25.680
Yep?

19:33.280 --> 19:37.194
Jesus, you still drunk from last night
or are you starting a new bender?

19:37.440 --> 19:41.070
Yeah, okay. Yeah, I said okay.

19:42.840 --> 19:44.991
Uh, I gotta go.

19:45.240 --> 19:47.436
Anything wrong?
It's fine. I just gotta go.

19:49.560 --> 19:51.119
Sure, some other time then.

19:53.880 --> 19:56.759
<i>I'll have to find another way
to get to him.</i>

20:04.000 --> 20:05.036
Ah, lieutenant.

20:05.240 --> 20:06.993
Tell me something.

20:07.200 --> 20:09.237
Did you decide
you don't need a sergeant?

20:09.440 --> 20:11.875
Sir?
I expected an announcement by now.

20:12.080 --> 20:13.116
What's going on?

20:13.800 --> 20:17.919
To tell you the truth, I'm having trouble
narrowing down my choice.

20:23.840 --> 20:27.311
I know you want me to pick Miller,
and on paper, I can't argue with that.

20:27.520 --> 20:30.319
Scored higher on the test,
got the experience, the record--

20:30.520 --> 20:32.398
She's African-American,
a woman.

20:32.600 --> 20:35.798
Here's the thing,
Quinn has his attributes too.

20:36.920 --> 20:37.956
Name one.

20:38.160 --> 20:39.196
He's street-smart.

20:40.200 --> 20:42.078
Look, I know what's going on here.

20:42.280 --> 20:44.556
What do you mean?
You want me to be the bad guy.

20:44.800 --> 20:46.996
You want me to insist
that you promote Miller.

20:47.200 --> 20:49.431
