Why do you look like someone
just ran over your dog?

40:57.320 --> 41:00.552
I just got off the phone with her
and she couldn't stop crying.

41:00.960 --> 41:02.474
She thinks it's all her fault,

41:02.680 --> 41:05.559
like somehow, she's not
good enough or something.

41:05.760 --> 41:08.719
Well, she would've caught him
cheating eventually.

41:08.920 --> 41:11.389
The result
would have been the same.

41:11.840 --> 41:15.151
Yeah, but it wouldn't be me
that made her cry.

41:16.160 --> 41:18.516
Jesus, I just feel like shit.

41:19.240 --> 41:21.232
People can't help
sticking their noses in

41:21.440 --> 41:23.193
when it's someone
they care about.

41:23.640 --> 41:25.313
I know.

41:25.520 --> 41:28.160
I know. You tried to tell me.

41:30.960 --> 41:32.952
So does that mean
you care about me?

41:34.400 --> 41:37.871
Only to the extent
that you sign my pay cheque.

41:40.280 --> 41:41.873
TouchÃ©.

41:42.080 --> 41:45.676
Okay, what are we gonna read tonight?
Let me guess, <i>Wee Monkeys.</i>

41:45.880 --> 41:47.473
<i>Wee Monkeys!</i>

41:57.280 --> 42:02.196
Before I read to you, I gotta
talk to you about the TV remote.

42:02.400 --> 42:03.800
You said you didn't take it,

42:04.040 --> 42:06.430
but Jamie found it
under your bed.

42:11.000 --> 42:12.354
I didn't mean to break it.

42:12.560 --> 42:14.597
I was pretending
it was a Thunder Blaster

42:14.840 --> 42:17.230
and I dropped it in the kitchen.

42:17.440 --> 42:19.352
Well, yeah, that's okay.
Accidents happen.

42:19.560 --> 42:21.279
But you lied to me.
That's a big deal.

42:21.480 --> 42:23.312
We should never lie.

42:27.280 --> 42:29.112
But, Daddy,

42:29.920 --> 42:31.752
you lie.

42:34.320 --> 42:36.073
What do you mean?

42:48.520 --> 42:51.080
You told me Doggy got lost.

42:51.280 --> 42:53.840
I saw you throw him in the trash.

42:54.040 --> 42:56.350
I had to rescue him.

43:01.000 --> 43:03.037
You're right. I lied.

43:04.640 --> 43:07.872
Doggy got dirty,
and I tried to clean him up,

43:08.080 --> 43:10.800
and when I couldn't,
I threw him away.

43:11.600 --> 43:13.910
I'm sorry I lied to you, Harrison.

43:14.120 --> 43:16.680
That's okay.
But can I keep him?

43:16.880 --> 43:18.519
I really love him.

43:18.720 --> 43:21.155
<i>He's soaked in blood
that links me to a murder.</i>

43:21.360 --> 43:24.114
Yeah, but maybe
he should live under the bed.

43:24.320 --> 43:26.551
Okay.
Okay.

43:26.760 --> 43:27.989
<i>Wee Monkeys.</i>

43:28.200 --> 43:30.157
<i>Wee Monkeys!</i>

43:30.360 --> 43:33.956
<i>It's no accident,
Harrison catching me in a lie.</i>

43:34.960 --> 43:37.350
<i>I can live with my lies,
but how long can Harrison</i>

43:37.560 --> 43:40.120
<i>before he finally sees through?</i>

43:40.360 --> 43:42.158
I should be back
in a few hours.

43:42.360 --> 43:45.114
Sorry to keep you late
on your birthday.

43:45.320 --> 43:48.119
Trust me, it'll probably be
the highlight of my day.

43:48.320 --> 43:51.518
<i>Vogel doesn't want me to kill Zach,
but she's wrong about him.</i>

43:51.720 --> 43:53.871
<i>He deserves nothing but my table.</i>

43:55.000 --> 43:56.798
<i>He's here.</i>

44:01.640 --> 44:02.756
Hey, Zach, it's Dexter.

44:26.400 --> 44:28.073
<i>Where is he?</i>

44:35.640 --> 44:39.395
<i>Why would Zach buy a car
for $1200?</i>

44:39.600 --> 44:42.115
<i>Because the one mistake
he made with Norma Rivera</i>

44:42.360 --> 44:44.750
<i>was showing up to kill her
in a red Porsche.</i>

44:44.960 --> 44:47.350
<i>He's going to kill Sofia tonight.</i>

45:04.680 --> 45:06.160
<i>Cypress Harbour Yacht Club.</i>
Hi.

45:06.360 --> 45:09.239
Could you tell me
if Sofia Fuentes is working tonight?

45:09.440 --> 45:12.194
<i>She gets off here in a few minutes.</i>
Thank you.

45:32.240 --> 45:35.233
<i>Zach, waiting to make his move.</i>

45:45.680 --> 45:49.071
<i>And Quinn,
still trying to prove he's a good cop.</i>

45:59.960 --> 46:01.792
Hey, Dex.
<i>Hey.</i>

46:02.000 --> 46:05.357
Look, this is probably
none of my business,

46:05.560 --> 46:08.280
but I feel like I should
tell you about Quinn.

46:08.960 --> 46:09.996
Okay.

46:10.240 --> 46:12.197
He thinks you're gonna
break up with him.

46:12.400 --> 46:13.800
<i>Break up with him? Why?</i>

46:14.040 --> 46:15.838
Because he didn't make sergeant.

46:16.840 --> 46:18.069
That's crazy.

46:18.280 --> 46:19.430
Why would he think that?

46:19.640 --> 46:23.714
Maybe you should, um, invite him over.
I think he's feeling pretty down.

46:23.960 --> 46:25.758
<i>Yeah. Yeah, of course.</i>

46:26.240 --> 46:29.392
Thanks, Dex, for calling.
That really is so sweet of you.

46:29.640 --> 46:30.790
Sure.

46:50.720 --> 46:53.280
<i>Quinn problem solved.</i>

46:55.040 --> 46:56.110
<i>And there's Sofia.</i>

47:04.040 --> 47:05.633
<i>Zach's father.</i>

47:07.000 --> 47:11.199
<i>Sofia is Hamilton's mistress,
just like Norma before her.</i>

47:38.480 --> 47:40.437
<i>What is he doing?</i>

48:12.640 --> 48:13.790
Hey.

48:14.000 --> 48:15.559
I know what you're doing.

48:15.760 --> 48:16.955
Quinn.

48:17.640 --> 48:20.109
You playing detective?
Watching Zach?

48:22.440 --> 48:23.794
Yeah, you caught me.

48:24.040 --> 48:27.477
I'm going to see Jamie.
Keep an eye on Zach.

48:35.680 --> 48:38.434
Jesus. What the fuck?

48:38.680 --> 48:40.512
What are you doing?

48:43.320 --> 48:45.676
Why were you going
to kill your father?

48:45.880 --> 48:49.396
What? I wasn't trying to kill my--
I know you killed Norma Rivera.

48:49.600 --> 48:53.230
I thought you were going to kill Sofia,
but you were going after your father.

48:53.440 --> 48:55.159
Why?
You're crazy.

48:55.360 --> 48:57.875
I didn't try and kill my father.

48:58.520 --> 49:01.194
You tell me one more lie,
and I'll kill you.

49:03.200 --> 49:04.793
I had to.

49:05.040 --> 49:07.191
Why?
Because he's killing my mother.

49:08.360 --> 49:11.432
She's drinking herself to death
because of him.

49:11.840 --> 49:13.797
Over the years,
one affair after another,

49:14.000 --> 49:16.560
and he doesn't
even try and hide it.

49:17.320 --> 49:19.152
I thought killing Norma
would put an end to it,

49:19.320 --> 49:21.232
but two days later,

49:21.440 --> 49:23.557
he's banging some hostess
from the club.

49:25.040 --> 49:26.713
I knew if I wanted it to stop,

49:26.920 --> 49:29.116
I had to kill Dad.

49:31.640 --> 49:33.791
So that's what this is all about,

49:34.000 --> 49:36.469
you trying to protect your mother?

49:36.800 --> 49:38.473
You actually care about her?

49:39.120 --> 49:41.351
Of course I do. She's my mother.

49:45.240 --> 49:48.438
But showing up at crime scenes,

49:49.560 --> 49:51.836
accidents,

49:53.080 --> 49:54.753
taking pictures of all the blood.

49:54.960 --> 49:56.792
This is about more than
just your mother.

49:57.000 --> 49:58.559
No, I had to protect her.

49:58.800 --> 50:01.190
Yeah, I believe you.

50:01.640 --> 50:04.030
But you killed because you want to kill.
No.

50:04.360 --> 50:06.272
Yes.

50:08.200 --> 50:10.760
To take a living person

50:11.680 --> 50:13.751
and make them dead,

50:15.720 --> 50:18.713
imagining that you can
actually hear the moment

50:18.920 --> 50:21.310
when their heart stops beating,

50:22.280 --> 50:25.876
smell the blood
as it pools across the floor.

50:30.960 --> 50:32.872
I can't help it.

50:36.320 --> 50:38.960
It just builds up inside me

50:39.280 --> 50:41.272
all these years.

50:41.480 --> 50:44.234
But Norma was the first time
I ever followed through.

50:44.440 --> 50:46.318
And how was it,

50:46.960 --> 50:48.440
once you'd killed her?

50:50.600 --> 50:54.116
It felt like this huge weight

50:54.360 --> 50:56.636
was lifted off my chest,

50:56.840 --> 51:02.154
this release of something
horrible inside me.

51:04.840 --> 51:07.435
Like you were finally in control.

51:07.640 --> 51:09.279
Yes.

51:15.480 --> 51:17.949
You should just
go ahead and kill me.

51:19.960 --> 51:20.996
Why?

51:21.200 --> 51:23.840
Because if you don't,
I know I'll do it again.

51:27.000 --> 51:31.279
I don't want to be like this,
but I can't help it.

51:33.040 --> 51:34.679
I just am.

51:34.880 --> 51:36.872
I'm some kind of freak.

51:37.080 --> 51:38.799
A monster.

51:39.800 --> 51:41.234
Yes.

51:43.880 --> 51:45.872
You haven't told anyone else
about this?

51:46.120 --> 51:48.077
Besides Dr. Vogel.

51:48.280 --> 51:50.920
No, I couldn't.

51:51.480 --> 51:53.949
You never had a Harry.

51:55.040 --> 51:56.713
A what?

51:57.200 --> 51:59.396
Someone to talk to.

52:02.840 --> 52:04.957
Someone to teach you.

52:08.200 --> 52:10.396
<i>Some things happen to us
by accident.</i>

52:10.640 --> 52:13.792
<i>Others are choices.</i>

52:14.280 --> 52:17.352
<i>There are parts of me that I can
never share with my own son.</i>

52:17.560 --> 52:19.438
<i>But with Zach,</i>

52:19.960 --> 52:21.838
<i>could I teach him?</i>

52:22.040 --> 52:24.077
<i>Am I ready for this,</i>

52:24.320 --> 52:27.199
<i>to be a spiritual father?</i>

52:30.520 --> 52:34.400
So how'd your sting go with Elway?

52:36.160 --> 52:37.958
Terribly.

52:38.680 --> 52:40.433
Didn't work out?

52:41.040 --> 52:43.430
No, it worked out fine, but--

52:44.040 --> 52:45.633
What?

52:48.480 --> 52:50.233
He likes me.

52:50.600 --> 52:52.034
Oh.

52:52.640 --> 52:53.790
That's a bad thing?

52:54.000 --> 52:57.516
Well, he likes me because he doesn't
know a fucking thing about me.

52:58.400 --> 53:02.474
"Yeah, I killed two people
and tried to kill myself and my brother.

53:02.680 --> 53:05.195
But, sorry, what kind of wine
would you like to order?"

53:05.400 --> 53:08.120
I mean, what the fuck?

53:08.320 --> 53:11.677
Yeah, I kind of know what you mean.

53:11.880 --> 53:14.156
How are things with Cassie?

53:15.080 --> 53:16.514
Um...

53:17.360 --> 53:19.477
I don't think there's
much of a future there.

53:19.680 --> 53:22.514
Maybe the Morgans just
aren't meant for relationships.

53:22.760 --> 53:24.797
Yeah, maybe not.

53:27.880 --> 53:29.109
But, hey, life is good.

53:29.320 --> 53:31.755
I'm feeling optimistic
for the first time in a while.

53:31.960 --> 53:34.839
I'm even thinking about
taking on a kind of...

53:35.360 --> 53:36.840
Intern.

53:38.040 --> 53:39.554
Hm...

53:40.920 --> 53:42.877
Well, that's a big step for you, right?

53:43.080 --> 53:47.040
Letting some novice
into your private lab.

53:47.280 --> 53:48.794
Yeah.

53:51.640 --> 53:53.597
Hey, are you okay?

53:53.800 --> 53:55.951
I don't feel so good.

53:56.640 --> 53:58.438
What's wrong?

53:58.800 --> 54:01.076
I feel kind of dizzy.

54:01.280 --> 54:02.634
Deb?

54:08.040 --> 54:09.952
Hello, Dexter.

54:14.000 --> 54:15.957
Remember me?
